        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="194" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d194">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 <gloss target="#t_EW1">E.
                    W.</gloss>/6–2945</note>
                <head>No. 194 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the British Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_H1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Halifax</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-07">July 7,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Lord <persName corresp="#p_H1">Halifax</persName>
                    </hi>: I have your letter of June 29<note n="1" xml:id="d194fn1">
                        <ref target="#d176">Document No. 176</ref>.</note> proposing that the
                    subject of “war criminals” be discussed at the next meeting of Heads of
                    Governments.</p>
                <p>The question is being given careful consideration by this Government. Much will
                    depend undoubtedly on the discussions now taking place in London between
                    representatives of the British, United States, French and Soviet
                    Governments.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Joseph C. Grew</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
